CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1956, page 16, reads: "1. Thousands Of Interested Homemakers filed in when the doors of the Syria Mosque opened heralding the opening of The Pittsburgh Courier's fifth annual Home Service Fair, March 27-29. They were greeted by the Dodge dealer who signed them up for a chance to win a new 1956 Dodge Royal Lancer."
TitMainTitle: Crowd gathered at registration table in Dodge car booth in Syria Mosque for the 1956 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
